metadata.name: Mícheál—Flesh Of My Flesh
metadata.description:
I seek to paint figures that suffer as inconvenience a situ of tireless seeking 
non beings reminiscent of feelings
images suffocating from vastness 
remaining still and alone
figures that recede into spaces 
not unlike memory in proximity with shadows cast in cold light and voluminous 
nondescript textures figures attempting 
to avoid identification presenting human contexts and anatomical insinuation 
with geological indications shapes are of nature emergent and inevitable
lost in continuums of time 
and space figures possessed by presence 
in a vacuum with untitled tendencies
appearing with traces of a name suggesting namelessness attempting to compose a decomposition to halt a procession to be within from a distance
biological and anthropological 
and still manifest as assemblage
figures born into arbitrary dying from certainty toward uncertainty presenting a limited view of a limiting relationship 
with solitude
